From late 1965 to 1968 McGuire was the bass guitarist, alongside Green on guitar, in the Questions, which were a "musically substantial bunch" and they released their debut album, What Is a Question?, in October 1966.

Early in 1967 Doug Parkinson joined on lead vocals, it was his first major band, the line up also included Ray Burton on guitar and Doug Lavery on drums – both later joined the Valentines and Axiom – and Rory Thomas on Hammond organ.
The Questions entered the 1967 Hoadley's Battle of the Sounds and won the New South Wales state final, they competed in Melbourne for the Australian final finishing second to the Groop.

In September 1970 McGuire was a founding member of a progressive rock band, King Harvest, with Leo de Castro on lead vocals and lead guitar (ex-Leo and the Browns, Leo and Friends); Jimmy Doyle on guitar (Silhouettes, Aesop's Fables, Moonstone); Mark Kennedy on drums (Spectrum); and Steve Yates on keyboards (ex-Rush, Expression).
